# Flutter 3 Cursor Rules

## Architecture
- Use layered architecture: Presentation → Domain → Data
- Keep widgets small and focused (under 100 lines)
- Extract business logic into providers/blocs — widgets are UI only
- Use `go_router` for declarative routing

## Widgets
- Prefer `StatelessWidget` — use `StatefulWidget` only when managing local state
- Composition over inheritance — combine small widgets
- Use `const` constructors for performance
- Name widgets descriptively: `UserProfileCard`, `SettingsToggle`

## State Management
- Simple: `ValueNotifier` + `ValueListenableBuilder`
- Medium: `Riverpod` (recommended) or `Provider`
- Complex: `Bloc` / `Cubit` for event-driven state
- Use `AsyncNotifier` for async operations in Riverpod

## Performance
- Use `const` widgets wherever possible
- Use `ListView.builder()` for long lists (lazy rendering)
- Avoid rebuilding entire widget trees — use selective state management
- Use `RepaintBoundary` for complex animations
- Profile with Flutter DevTools

## Platform Conventions
- Follow Material Design 3 on Android, Cupertino on iOS
- Use `Platform.isIOS` / `Platform.isAndroid` for platform checks
- Use `adaptive` widgets when available
- Handle safe areas with `SafeArea` widget
